av|Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav]], Grand Cross (Norway)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Royal Order of the Sword - Commander Grand Cross BAR.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Order of the Sword|Royal Order of the Sword]], Commander Grand Cross (Sweden)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Orden al M\u00e9rito Naval (Venezuela) - ribbon bar.png|width=80}}\n|[[Order of Naval Merit (Venezuela)|Order of Naval Merit]], First Class (Venezuela)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=VPD National Order of Vietnam - Commander BAR.svg|width=80}}\n|[[National Order of Vietnam]], Third Class (Republic of Vietnam)\n|-\n|[[File:Vietnam Chuong My Medal ribbon-First Class.svg|80px]]\n|[[Chuong My Medal]], 1st Class\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Vietnam Navy Distinguished Service Order Ribbon-First Class.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Vietnam Distinguished Service Order|Republic of Vietnam Navy Distinguished Service Order]], First Class (Republic of Vietnam)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Vietnam Gallantry Cross, with palm.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Republic of Vietnam Gallantry Cross]] with Palm (Republic of Vietnam)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=2|type=service-star|ribbon=Phliber rib.png|width=80}}\n|[[Philippine Liberation Medal]] with two service stars (Philippines)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=United Nations Service Medal ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[United Nations Korea Medal]]\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Vietnam Campaign Medal ribbon with 60- clasp.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Vietnam Campaign Medal]] (Republic of Vietnam)\n|}\n\n===Foreign unit awards===\n{|\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Presidential Unit Citation (Philippines).svg|width=80}}\n|[[Philippine Presidential Unit Citation]] (Philippines)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Presidential Unit Citation (Korea).svg|width=80}}\n|[[Korean Presidential Unit Citation]] (Republic of Korea)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Vietnam gallantry cross unit award-3d.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Republic of Vietnam Gallantry Cross]] Unit Citation (Republic of Vietnam)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=VNCivilActionsRibbon-2.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Vietnam Civil Actions Unit Citation]] (Republic of Vietnam)\n|}\n\n===Boy Scouts of America awards===\n{|\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=oak|ribbon=DESA ribbon.png|width=80}}\n|[[Distinguished Eagle Scout Award]]\n|}\n\n==Miscellaneous==\n* Zumwalt's picture hangs in the [[War Remnants Museum (Ho Chi Minh City)|War Remnants Museum]] in Ho Chi Minh City, near pictures of [[John Kerry]], [[Robert McNamara]], [[Warren Christopher]], and other American dignitaries, in commemoration of a visit he made after normalization of relations between Vietnam and the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daily.nysun.com/Repository/getmailfiles.asp?Style%3DOliveXLib%3AArticleToMail%26Type%3Dtext%2Fhtml%26Path%3DNYS%2F2004%2F08%2F16%26ID%3DAr00100 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=February 9, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060516203647/http://daily.nysun.com/Repository/getmailfiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib%3AArticleToMail&Type=text%2Fhtml&Path=NYS%2F2004%2F08%2F16&ID=Ar00100 |archivedate=May 16, 2006 }}</ref>\n* In his first book, ''On Watch'', Zumwalt quoted at length an interview with Admiral [[Hyman G. Rickover]], regarded as the [[Father of the Nuclear Navy]] and who interviewed all officers with responsibilities involving nuclear propulsion. Rickover and Zumwalt had a combative conversation, with Zumwalt referring to it as a humbling experience.\n* Zumwalt was a member of [[Sigma Phi Epsilon]] fraternity. He was initiated in 1980.{{Citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n* In 1994 the U.S. Navy Memorial Foundation awarded Zumwalt its Lone Sailor Award for his distinguished naval career.\n* In 1972, Zumwalt became an honorary member of the [[Royal Swedish Society of Naval Sciences]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.koms.se/content/uploads/2013/06/TiS-nr-4-1996.pdf |journal=Tidskrift i sj\u00f6v\u00e4sendet |title=Matrikel 1996 f\u00f6r Kungl. \u00d6rlogsmannas\u00e4llskapet |year=1996 |number=4 |publisher=Tidskrift i sj\u00f6v\u00e4sendet |location=Carlskrona |format=PDF |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|8258455}} |page=313}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Biography|World War II}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* ''My Father, My Son'' by Elmo R. Zumwalt Jr. and Elmo R. Zumwalt III, with [[John Pekkanen]]. (Dell Publishing Company, {{ISBN|0-440-15973-3}})\n* ''On Watch: a memoir'' by Elmo R. Zumwalt Jr. (The New York Times Book Co., {{ISBN|0-8129-0520-2}})\n* ''Admiral Elmo R. Zumwalt Jr., Texas Tech University Series'' [http://www.virtualarchive.vietnam.ttu.edu/cgi-bin/starfetch.exe?N4@s13Nbkp6bg29BrFO1pNZvr0DdFDSjye3yUDRVsV6Ke0GZcmbVZhkmoBkfSLgLY9RC5Rqs0Us4tQAivQKzlsyfJEfo4pVehbpFTLDZjAE/6310000000.pdf Texas Tech University's Virtual Vietnam archive]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Elmo Zumwalt}}\n* {{Find a Grave|20677|accessdate=2008-07-13}}\n* [http://www.history.navy.mil/faqs/faq93-2.htm Z-grams: A List of Policy Directives Issued by Admiral Zumwalt 1 July 1970 to 1 July 1974]\n* [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,944519-1,00.html 1972 Time magazine article on resistance to Zumwalt's policies, \"Keelhauling the Navy\"]\n* [http://www.usni.org/heritage/zumwalt.asp Zumwalt, ADM Elmo R. Jr., U.S. Navy (Ret.)]\n* [http://www.usni.org/heritage/ZumwaltStaffOfficersVolumeI.asp Zumwalt Staff Officers, Volume I]\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/opinion/2014/04/13/me-and-z-admiral-zumwalt/|title=Me and \"Z\" \u2013 Admiral Elmo R. Zumwalt &#124; Fox News|publisher=foxnews.com|accessdate=2014-07-12}}\n*{{C-SPAN|Elmo Zumwalt}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Thomas H. Moorer]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Chief of Naval Operations]]|years=1970\u20131974}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[James L. Holloway III]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zumwalt, Elmo}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:2000 deaths]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:People from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:Virginia Democrats]]\n[[Category:American naval personnel of the Vietnam War]]\n[[Category:American naval personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Chiefs of Naval Operations]]\n[[Category:Deaths from mesothelioma]]\n[[Category:Distinguished Eagle Scouts]]\n[[Category:National War College alumni]]\n[[Category:Naval War College alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Arlington County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:United States Naval Academy alumni]]\n[[Category:United States Navy admirals]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Navy Distinguished Service Medal]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Legion of Merit]]\n[[Category:Presidential Medal of Freedom recipients]]\n[[Category:Order of May]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Naval Merit (Brazil)]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses of the Order of the Southern Cross]]\n[[Category:Order of Naval Merit Admiral Padilla]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses with Silver Breast Star of the Order of Merit of Duarte, S\u00e1nchez and Mella]]\n[[Category:Commandeurs of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses with Star and Sash of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses of the Order of George I]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Merit of the Italian Republic]]\n[[Category:Grand Cordons of the Order of the Rising Sun]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Military Merit (Korea)]]\n[[Category:Order of National Security Merit members]]\n[[Category:Grand Officers of the Order of Orange-Nassau]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Sword]]\n[[Category:Recipients of t